  "text": "• C with a Branson model B-12 sonifier, for 120 s (30 s pulses) at 70 W. Cy. paradoxa cells and cyanelles were disrupted by osmotic shock and ultrasonic treatment respectively, as described previously [CITATION_1] . Plant leaves were sliced, suspended in buffer, as described above, and mechanically disrupted with a Waring blender. Cell-free extracts were obtained by centrifugation of homogenates at 40 000 g for 20 min.",
